Key Takeaways
Tokens are the smallest units of text processed by an LLM.
Embeddings convert text into numerical vectors that capture meaning.
Transformers process relationships between all tokens simultaneously.
Attention helps the model focus on the most relevant information.
Context Window defines how much information the model can remember during a conversation.
Temperature controls the randomness and creativity of the model's responses.
Hallucinations occur when the model confidently generates incorrect information.
RAG improves accuracy by retrieving relevant external information before generating a response.

